**Inline comments:** Strategic comments in complex logic (e.g., DAG scheduling, review arbiter, decomposition detection) explain the "why", not just "what".

### 7. DATABASE & JSON HANDLING - 7/10

**Database layer is well-typed:**

Example from `/src/factory/db/issues.rs`:
```rust
fn row_to_issue(row: &Row) -> Result<Issue> {
    let column_name: String = row.get(4)?;
    let priority_str: String = row.get(6)?;

    let column = IssueColumn::from_str(&column_name)
        .map_err(|e| anyhow::anyhow!(e))
        .context("Failed to parse issue column")?;
    let priority = Priority::from_str(&priority_str)
        .map_err(|e| anyhow::anyhow!(e))
        .context("Failed to parse issue priority")?;
    // ... proper error context at each step
}
```

**Strong points:**
- Explicit type conversions at boundaries
- `.context()` enrichment on every parse failure
- Proper use of `Result` types

**Weakness:**
- String-based column indexing (fragile), though mitigated by compile-time constant ISSUE_COLS

